claim.claim-text:
15. A system comprising:
one or more processors;
one or more computer-readable storage memories embodying computer-readable instructions which, when executed by the one or more processors, implement a method comprising:
identifying at least one hyperlink displayed in a webpage, the at least one hyperlink being associated with a target webpage;
determining at least one style to be applied to the webpage based at least in part upon information associated with the target webpage, the at least one style comprising a mouse indicator; and
visually applying said at least one style to the webpage, without causing navigation of an associated browser to the target webpage,
wherein the information associated with the target webpage of the at least one hyperlink comprising information regarding a domain hosting the target webpage,
wherein said identifying comprises identifying multiple hyperlinks at least some of which being associated with different target webpages;
wherein said determining comprises determining multiple respective styles to be applied to the webpage based at least upon information associated with said different respective target webpages; and
wherein said visually applying comprises applying said multiple respective styles to the webpage, the multiple respective styles comprising different respective styles.
